This weathered signpost reads:
TETHIR ROAD / TEJARN ROAD

Tejarn Road - North
Tejarn Gate - East
Brost - West

These lands belong to the Tejarn Tower and honorable Lord-Knight Iybn Sahkr el Agis of the Tejarn Gate. Please approach cautiously, the road ahead is troublesome.

The Tejarn Tower is hiring, inquire with Sir Sabin Anoeta if interested.

This ancient looking stone is covered in lichen and marks from travelers long since past and dead. Still, engraved much deeper than anyone can defile is the name of the road the person is traveling upon...
Tejarn Mines - Property of the Lords of Tejarn Gate for the benefit of King Alemander
Tejarn Mines - Property of the Lords of Tejarn Gate for the benefit of King Alemander

Value.value: Your proficiency in history tells you that King Alemander was the last King of Tethyr before the Interregnum. These mines have been in a state of disuse since the Queen-Monarch, Zaranda Star, ascended to the throne of Tethyr...
A lone man trying his luck on travelers braving the Tethir Road...
